Titolo: Das Boot (video game)

Anno: 1990

Descrizione: Das Boot: German U-boat Simulation is a submarine simulator game designed by Paul Butler & Rick Banks and published in 1990 for Amiga and MS-DOS systems by Three-Sixty Pacific.  It was inspired by the book of the same name.
The player takes command of a German Type VII U-boat and plays missions against the Allies which involve combat against aircraft, anti-submarine warships, and other submarines.
The game was touted to feature 256 VGA Color, 3D Views, and historical realism.

Genere: Submarine simulator

Valutazione: N/A
